spec: socket_extra158
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(socket)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html — Python socket module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/socket.py"
    - "CPython source: Modules/socketmodule.c"
    - "socket_extra157.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.IPPROTO_TCP.__eq__(6) / IPPROTO_UDP.__eq__(17) / IPPROTO_IP.__eq__(0) / IPPROTO_TCP.__class__.__name__.__eq__('int') / SOL_SOCKET.__eq__(65535) / SO_REUSEADDR.__class__.__name__.__eq__('int') / SO_KEEPALIVE.__class__.__name__.__eq__('int') / SO_REUSEADDR.__eq__(4) / SO_KEEPALIVE.__eq__(8) (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.__spec__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('ModuleSpec') / __spec__.name.__eq__('socket') / socket.socket makefile/__setblocking/__settimeout/__getpeername/__getsockname/__setsockopt qualnames and lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "socket_extra155.zspec.zsdl — covers socket.setdefaulttimeout/__class__.__name__/__module__ / getdefaulttimeout/__class__.__name__ / gethostname/__class__.__name__/__module__ / getaddrinfo/__class__.__name__/__module__ / socket.socket.__doc__/__class__.__name__ (table + invariants)."
    - "socket.zspec / early extras — cover socket.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in socket_extra93 through socket_extra157."
    - "Wave 340 theme: socket.AF_INET / AF_INET6 / SOCK_STREAM / SOCK_DGRAM constant values and IntEnum class identity — AF_INET.__eq__(2) / AF_INET6.__eq__(30) / SOCK_STREAM.__eq__(1) / SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) / AF_INET.__class__.__name__.__eq__('AddressFamily') / SOCK_STREAM.__class__.__name__.__eq__('SocketKind') — macOS-specific values for AF_INET6."
    - "socket.AF_INET == 2. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.AF_INET6 == 30 (macOS-specific). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SOCK_STREAM == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SOCK_DGRAM == 2. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.AF_INET6.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SOCK_STREAM.__class__.__name__ == 'SocketKind'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__class__.__name__ == 'SocketKind'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: socket.AF_INET == 2 (POSIX-standardized; cross-platform). AF_INET is the address family for IPv4 sockets. Its value 2 is consistent across Linux, macOS, and Windows. socket.AF_INET6 == 30 on macOS (platform-specific; Linux uses 10). AF_INET6 is the address family for IPv6 sockets. Both AF_INET and AF_INET6 are members of the socket.AddressFamily IntEnum (Python 3.4+). This contrasts with IPPROTO_* constants which are plain int (not IntEnum) — extra157 anchors IPPROTO_TCP.__class__.__name__=='int'."
    - "Note: socket.SOCK_STREAM == 1 and socket.SOCK_DGRAM == 2. SOCK_STREAM (value 1) is the socket type for TCP-style reliable, ordered, bidirectional byte-stream connections. SOCK_DGRAM (value 2) is the socket type for UDP-style unreliable datagrams. Both are members of the socket.SocketKind IntEnum (Python 3.4+). SOCK_STREAM(1) < SOCK_DGRAM(2). The values 1 and 2 are POSIX-standardized and cross-platform."
    - "Note: socket.AF_INET.__class__.__name__ == 'AddressFamily' (13 chars). socket.SOCK_STREAM.__class__.__name__ == 'SocketKind' (10 chars). AF_INET and AF_INET6 are AddressFamily IntEnum members. SOCK_STREAM and SOCK_DGRAM are SocketKind IntEnum members. These IntEnum types were introduced in Python 3.4 (PEP 435). They are subclasses of int (issubclass(AddressFamily, int) == True) and enum.IntEnum. The class names 'AddressFamily' (13 chars) and 'SocketKind' (10 chars) are longer than 'int' (3 chars) used for IPPROTO_* constants."
    - "Note: socket.SOCK_DGRAM.__eq__(2) == True and socket.AF_INET.__eq__(2) == True. These two constants both equal 2 but have different types (SocketKind vs AddressFamily). This illustrates that IntEnum values are integers and can be compared by value; the type context (AF or SOCK) gives the constant its semantic meaning."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

